<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911203-0044</DOCNO><DOCID>911203-0044.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Anderson Exploration Ltd.:   Firm to Pay $96.5 Million   For a Columbia Gas Unit</HL><DATE>12/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9</SO><CO>   CG T.AXL</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)GAS UTILITIES (GAS)OIL-SECONDARY (OIS)PETROLEUM (PET)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>BANKRUPTCY DECLARATIONS AND PROCEEDINGS (BCY)PETROLEUM MARKET (PET)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CANADA (CN)DELAWARE (DE)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Anderson Exploration Ltd. said it agreed to buy theCanadian subsidiary of Columbia Gas System Inc. for 109.5million Canadian dollars (US$96.5 million).   Columbia Gas, which has been operating under bankruptcycourt protection since last summer, announced the transactionlast month but declined to specify terms until the definitiveagreement had been submitted to the bankruptcy court forapproval.</LP><TEXT>   Anderson said the Canadian subsidiary, Columbia GasDevelopment of Canada Ltd., has current production of about1,560 barrels a day of oil and natural gas liquids and 34million cubic feet a day of natural gas. Anderson, ofCalgary, Alberta, produced an average 77 million cubic feetof gas and 5,428 barrels of oil daily in its fiscal yearended Oct. 30.   Columbia Gas System, Wilmington, Del., filed for Chapter11 status in July because of the financial strain fromthousands of high-priced gas supply contracts.</TEXT></DOC>